  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Distribution of Shelter &amp;amp; Food Kits to 120 households (480 beneficiaries)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The severe tropical storm Berguitta affected Mauritius from 16 to 18 January, strengthening to category 3 on the 17th. The centre of the storm passed at about 10 km off the South-Eastern coast of Mauritius by 18 January, causing heavy showers and increase in wind gusts to up to 120 km.

While most of the island has been spared the worst, some 4000 people have had to leave their homes to seek shelter in 71 refugee centres due to flooding, mudslides and damages to their houses.The most affected regions are the north, south and southeast as well as informal settlements in regions at risk of landslides and flooding.</narrative>
  </description>
